1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
3 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
FOR
5
6
7 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to daylight saving time; creating the
Wyman West Actual Lock the Clock Act; amending
9 Section 1, Chapter 161, O.S.L. 2024 (25 O.S. Supp.
2024, Section 90.29), which relates to daylight
10 saving standard; mandating year-round standard time;
providing for noncodification; and providing an
11 effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
16 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
17 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Wyman West
18 Actual Lock the Clock Act".
19 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 161, O.S.L.
20 2024 (25 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 90.29), is amended to read as
21 follows:
22 Section 90.29. A. If a federal law is passed that authorizes
23 states to observe daylight saving time year-round, Upon returning
24 to Standard Time on November 2, 2025, this state shall adopt
Req. No. 13284 Page 1
1 dayl ight saving standard time as the year-round standard of time for
2 the entire state and all its political subdivisions.
3 B. This section shall not be construed to affect the standard
4 time established by federal law governing the movement of common
5 carriers engaged in interstate commerce or the time for performance
6 of an act by an officer or department of the United States, as
7 established by a statute, lawful order, rule, or regulation of the
8 United States or an agency thereof.
9 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
